Brooklyn Vehicle Collision Analysis¶

Data imported from Google BigQuery by saving query results as follows:

1: nyc_collisions: Saving 'nypd_mv_collisions' table in a GCP bucket and then downloading as a .csv file

2: Street Report: select on_street_name, sum(number_of_persons_killed) total_died from [bigquery-public-data:new_york.nypd_mv_collisions] where on_street_name not in ('','Unspecified') and lower(borough) = 'brooklyn' group by on_street_name order by 2 DESC

3: Contr_factor_report: select contributing_factor_vehicle_1, count(*) total_collisions from [bigquery-public-data:new_york.nypd_mv_collisions] where contributing_factor_vehicle_1 not in ('','Unspecified') and lower(borough) = 'brooklyn' group by contributing_factor_vehicle_1 order by 2 DESC

@author- Akshay Koul @Date- 02/10/2020

In [22]:
# Building Seasonal ARIMA model
p = d = q = range(0, 2)
pdq = list(itertools.product(p, d, q))
seasonal_arimapdq = [(i[0], i[1], i[2], 12) for i in list(itertools.product(p, d, q))]
for par in pdq:
    for par_seas in seasonal_arimapdq:
        try:
            model = sm.tsa.statespace.SARIMAX(time_series,order=par,seasonal_order=par_seas,enforce_stationarity=False,
                                            enforce_invertibility=False)
            model_results = model.fit()
            print('ARIMA{}x{}12 - AIC:{}'.format(par, par_seas, model_results.aic))
        except:
            continue
